    "url": "http://localhost:4000/sta-blog//sto-weekly-review-by-evercity-713.01.2019/",
    "title": "STO Weekly Review by Evercity 7‚Äì13.01.2019",
    "body": "2019/01/15 - Projects üí∞Cadence, an investment platform for digital debt securities, has issued its first tokenized fixed income security. The debt product is in partnership with a marketplace lender extending working capital to e-commerce merchants. üñºSwarm fund reached soft cap for security token offering of The Art Token at $16 million raised. üìùSecurity token trading platform tZERO won a patent for a ‚ÄúCrypto Integration Platform‚Äù, described as having the capability to merge legacy trading systems with digital asset technology. ‚û°Ô∏èSharesPost, the registered BD, ATS, and RIA, has executed its first secondary transaction of security tokens. The tokens, which run on top of Ethereum, represent shares in the Blockchain Capital III Digital Liquid Venture Fund (BCAP). Regulation üá™üá∫The European Securities and Markets Authority (ESMA) published its Advice to the European Union (EU) Institutions‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäCommission, Council and Parliament‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääon initial coin offerings and crypto-assets. The Advice clarifies the existing EU rules applicable to crypto-assets that qualify as financial instruments, and provides ESMA‚Äôs position on any gaps and issues in the current EU financial regulatory framework for consideration by EU policymakers. Join Security Token Club: https://t. me/stoaccelerator "
