    "body": "2018/09/10 - STO Weekly Review by Evercity 03‚Äì09. 09. 2018: Main news üé®Warhol and tokens: 31,5% of the artist‚Äôs masterpiece ¬´14 small electric chairs¬ª was tokenised and sold to 100 investors via art investments platform Maecenas. The auction raised $1,7 million. Projects ü§ù0x‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääopen protocol that enables p2p token trading‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääannounced its alliance with Harbor, compliance-service for security tokens backed by former COO of digital payments giant PayPal David Sacks. As a part of the partnership, David joined 0x team as advisor. üá¶üá∫Australian Stock Exchange (ASX) postpones its switch to blockchain for equity transactions for 6 months. The exchange has been working since the end of 2017 on implementation of blockchain tech to fully replace their existent transactions system, üå¥Security Token Offering of an island: Great Keppel Island aims to become a biggest island crypto micro-economy of the world with a luxe resort, private real estate and golf fields. Investors will soon be invited to buy security tokens of the island. The project aims to attract $300 million for construction. Regulations üá∫üá∏California state legislature adopted a bill that legalises application of blockchain technology and smart contracts in national and international commerce. The bill also introduces changes into ¬´electronic record¬ª and ¬´electronic signature¬ª terms, allowing operation that are carried out via distributed ledger technologies. Join Security Token Accelerator &amp; Club https://t. me/stoaccelerator "
